HEADWORD: Stoolball
<hw>Stool"ball`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of game
with balls, formerly common in England, esp. with young women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nausicaa⟦br⟧
With other virgins did at <qex>stoolball</qex> play.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoom</ent>⟦br⟧
